      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box\">\n<blockquote>20 Years After <b>U.S. Invasion</b>, Iraq Is a Freer Place, but Not a Hopeful One</blockquote><br/>\n<br/>\n纽约时报今年3月文章标题，在美国说美军入侵伊拉克不是什么问题，欧洲媒体说美军入侵伊拉克的更多。<br/>\n<br/>\n楼主说的其他情况不了解。<br/>\n<br/>\n<blockquote>\"Make love, not war\" is an anti-war slogan commonly associated with the American counterculture of the 1960s. It was used primarily by those who were opposed to the Vietnam War, but has been invoked in other anti-war contexts since, around the world.</blockquote><br/>\n<br/>\n补充，著名反越战口号\t\t</div>",
